  "texts": [
    "However, these works focus on stable traits or natural behavior.",
    "In contrast, our approach trains models to detect transient, external manipulations-a distinct capability requiring attention to anomalous activation patterns at specific moments in time.",
    "Mechanistic InterpretabilityMechanistic interpretability aims to reverse-engineer model components [Elhage et al., 2022, Conmy et al., 2023].",
    "We take a complementary \"introspection-first\" approach: training the model to report its own states.",
    "This makes the model a participant in its own interpretation, potentially guiding mechanistic analysis toward relevant features."
